<div id="open-source-page" v-cloak>
  <div purpose="landing-page-container">
    <div purpose="landing-page-content">


      <div purpose="landing-page-hero">
        <div purpose="page-hero-content">
          <div purpose="page-hero-headings">
            <h4>Open source MDM</h4>
            <h1>Open source. Open company. Open to everyone.</h1>
          </div>
          <div purpose="page-hero-text">
            <p>Every line of Fleet is public. Our handbook is public. Our roadmap is public. Transparency makes better software, and it builds better trust with the people who use it.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="button-row" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center">
            <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/fleetdm/fleet" target="_blank" no-icon>View on GitHub</a>
            <animated-arrow-button href="/docs">Read the docs</animated-arrow-button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div purpose="landing-page-section" class="pt-0">
        <div purpose="hero-terminal">
          <div purpose="terminal-block">
            <div purpose="terminal-bar">
              <span purpose="terminal-dot" class="dot-red"></span>
              <span purpose="terminal-dot" class="dot-yellow"></span>
              <span purpose="terminal-dot" class="dot-green"></span>
              <span purpose="terminal-filename">~/fleet</span>
            </div>
<pre purpose="terminal-body"><span purpose="tc"># Clone Fleet and run it locally</span>
<span purpose="tp">$</span> git clone <span purpose="ts">https://github.com/fleetdm/fleet.git</span>
<span purpose="tp">$</span> cd fleet && docker compose up
<span purpose="tc"># Fleet is now running at localhost:1337</span></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>Why open source matters for device management</h3>
          <p>Your device management platform sees everything on your endpoints. You should be able to see everything about it.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-cards">
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Inspect everything</p>
              <p>Security teams can audit exactly how devices are managed, how data flows, and what the agent does. No black boxes. Code you can read, test, and verify.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Every component public on GitHub</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">No vendor lock-in</p>
              <p>Your device configuration lives in Git, not a proprietary database. If you ever leave Fleet, your data and configuration come with you.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>YAML in your repo, not our cloud</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Community driven</p>
              <p>Fleet's roadmap is shaped by the community, not just paying customers. Feature requests, bug reports, and code contributions move the product forward for everyone.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Public roadmap in GitHub Issues</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Extend and customize</p>
              <p>Build integrations, automate workflows, and customize Fleet without waiting for vendor approval. The API is comprehensive, and the code is yours to read and adapt.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Full REST API and source access</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Transparency for end users</p>
              <p>Employees can see exactly what's monitored on their work devices. Fleet Desktop links to the source code so people know what their company sees, and what it doesn't.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Built-in trust for the people you support</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-card">
            <div purpose="card-body">
              <p purpose="card-title">Proven at scale</p>
              <p>Fleet runs in production at companies managing hundreds of thousands of endpoints. Open source doesn't mean hobbyist. It means software that earns trust through transparency.</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="card-footer">
              <p>Used by Stripe, Fastly, Gusto, and more</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-quote">
          <div purpose="quote-image">
            <img alt="Stripe logo" src="/images/social-proof-logo-stripe-67x32@2x.png">
          </div>
          <p purpose="quote-text">"We've been using Fleet for a few years at Stripe and we couldn't be happier. The fact that it's also open source made it easy for us to try it out, customise it to our needs, and seamlessly integrate it into our existing environment."</p>
          <div purpose="quote-author-info">
            <div purpose="quote-author-image">
              <img alt="Scott MacVicar" src="/images/testimonial-author-scott-macvicar-100x100@2x.png">
            </div>
            <div purpose="name-and-title">
              <p purpose="author-name">Scott MacVicar</p>
              <p purpose="author-title">Head of Developer Infrastructure and Corporate Technology</p>
              <p purpose="author-title">Stripe</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>What's public at Fleet</h3>
          <p>We don't just open source our code. We open source how we run the company.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="open-grid">
          <a purpose="open-card" href="https://github.com/fleetdm/fleet" target="_blank">
            <p purpose="open-card-title">Source code</p>
            <p>The complete Fleet codebase: server, agent (fleetd), CLI, and website. Source available with permissive licensing.</p>
            <span purpose="open-card-link">github.com/fleetdm/fleet</span>
          </a>
          <a purpose="open-card" href="/handbook">
            <p purpose="open-card-title">Company handbook</p>
            <p>How we run the company. Processes, policies, org structure, and rituals, all public and open for contributions.</p>
            <span purpose="open-card-link">fleetdm.com/handbook</span>
          </a>
          <a purpose="open-card" href="https://github.com/fleetdm/fleet/issues" target="_blank">
            <p purpose="open-card-title">Public roadmap</p>
            <p>Every feature request, bug report, and user story lives in GitHub Issues. See what's coming and influence what gets built.</p>
            <span purpose="open-card-link">GitHub Issues</span>
          </a>
          <a purpose="open-card" href="https://fleetdm.com/slack" target="_blank">
            <p purpose="open-card-title">Community Slack</p>
            <p>Join the Fleet community in osquery Slack and MacAdmins Slack. Ask questions, share ideas, and connect with other users.</p>
            <span purpose="open-card-link">Join the community</span>
          </a>
          <a purpose="open-card" href="/trust">
            <p purpose="open-card-title">Security practices</p>
            <p>Our security policies, responsible disclosure program, and SOC 2 reports. Documented and transparent.</p>
            <span purpose="open-card-link">Trust center</span>
          </a>
          <a purpose="open-card" href="/docs">
            <p purpose="open-card-title">Documentation</p>
            <p>Deployment guides, REST API reference, configuration reference, and integration guides. Written in the open.</p>
            <span purpose="open-card-link">fleetdm.com/docs</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image" class="d-flex flex-lg-row flex-column justify-content-between mx-auto align-items-start">
          <div purpose="feature-text" class="d-flex flex-column">
            <h3>Everyone can contribute</h3>
            <p>Fleet is built by a global community of contributors. Whether you're fixing a typo in the docs, building an integration, or filing a bug, every contribution moves the product forward.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist" class="flex-column d-flex">
              <p>Submit a pull request to fix a bug or ship a feature</p>
              <p>File an issue or share feedback in GitHub</p>
              <p>Improve the documentation or handbook</p>
              <p>Answer questions in community Slack channels</p>
              <p>Write a tutorial, give a talk, or record a video</p>
              <p>Build an osquery table or query pack</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="button-row" style="margin-top: 16px;">
              <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/fleetdm/fleet/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" target="_blank" no-icon>Contributor guide</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="terminal-block">
            <div purpose="terminal-bar">
              <span purpose="terminal-dot" class="dot-red"></span>
              <span purpose="terminal-dot" class="dot-yellow"></span>
              <span purpose="terminal-dot" class="dot-green"></span>
              <span purpose="terminal-filename">contributing.md</span>
            </div>
<pre purpose="terminal-body"><span purpose="tc"># Open a pull request in three steps</span>
<span purpose="tp">$</span> git checkout -b <span purpose="ts">my-improvement</span>
<span purpose="tp">$</span> git commit -m <span purpose="ts">"Fix typo in docs"</span>
<span purpose="tp">$</span> gh pr create

<span purpose="tc"># Your change is reviewed in the open,</span>
<span purpose="tc"># and shipped in the next release.</span></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="handbook-callout">
          <div purpose="handbook-content">
            <h4>The Fleet handbook</h4>
            <h2>Our company handbook is public, too</h2>
            <p>Fleet's handbook is the source of truth for how we run the company. From product decisions to customer support, it's in the open. Anyone can suggest an improvement.</p>
            <div purpose="button-row">
              <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/handbook">Read the handbook</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


    </div>
  </div>


  <div purpose="tweets-container" class="container-fluid px-md-0 pb-0 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
    <div purpose="section-heading" class="mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-3">What people are saying</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <scrollable-tweets :testimonials="testimonialsForScrollableTweets"></scrollable-tweets>


  <div purpose="bottom-gradient">
    <div purpose="page-container" class="container">
      <div purpose="bottom-cta" class="text-center">
        <h4>Open source MDM</h4>
        <h1>Try Fleet for yourself</h1>
        <p>The free version of Fleet will always be free. Spin it up in your homelab or deploy it across your organization.</p>
        <div purpose="button-row" style="margin-top: 32px;" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center mx-auto">
          <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/pricing">Get started</a>
          <animated-arrow-button href="/contact">Get a demo</animated-arrow-button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>


  <parallax-city></parallax-city>

</div>
